{'description': 'The Digital Twin system adheres to the **ISO 23247:2021 standard**, which defines a **reference architecture for manufacturing Digital Twins** across four parts: Overview, Reference Architecture, Digital Representation, and Information Exchange. **Relevant industry standards** include the **entity-based RA** (Part 2), where **Observable Manufacturing Elements (OMEs)** are mapped to **Digital Twin Entities** via **Data Collection and Device Control Entities**. The standard does not mandate specific **certification requirements** or **compliance frameworks**, but it enforces **interoperability** through modular **Functional Entities (FEs)**. While **OPC Unified Architecture (OPC UA)** is mentioned as a potential implementation for FEs, it is not a strict requirement. **Interoperability standards** are implied via the **entity-based design**, ensuring modular exchange of data and control signals between physical and digital components. No other standards (e.g., IEC 62264 for enterprise integration) are referenced.'}